        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="MRI of Rectal Cancer: Tumor Staging, Imaging Techniques, and                    Management" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Natally  Horvat" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Camila  Carlos Tavares                            Rocha" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Brunna  Clemente Oliveira" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Iva  Petkovska" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Marc                        J.  Gollub" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="In this review of rectal MRI techniques and rectal anatomy, the authors describe current concepts in rectal cancer management; demonstrate the role of rectal MRI in local staging, restaging, and re..." /><meta name="Description" content="In this review of rectal MRI techniques and rectal anatomy, the authors describe current concepts in rectal cancer management; demonstrate the role of rectal MRI in local staging, restaging, and re..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Rectal cancer is prone to local recurrence and systemic metastasis. However, owing to improvements in TNM staging and treatment, including a more widespread use of rectal MRI and increased radiolog..." /><meta name="Description" content="Rectal cancer is prone to local recurrence and systemic metastasis. However, owing to improvements in TNM staging and treatment, including a more widespread use of rectal MRI and increased radiolog..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content=" Radiological Society of North America " /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2019-02-15" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="180114" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.2019180114" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="url" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.